<sec id="id-b7656b1a-03af-4847-b19a-b9076ecd586a"><title><?fontoxml-change-deletion author-id="9276395" change-id="6c24e176-ffdd-4ea4-d5fe-0501d9c36f79" text="Analysis of the existing situation" timestamp="1671533977427"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8763689" change-id="eea69769-6c70-4453-bf0c-acbc89df8358" timestamp="1656534182161"?>What is a grievance mechanism?<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="eea69769-6c70-4453-bf0c-acbc89df8358"?></title><?fontoxml-change-deletion author-id="9276395" change-id="ba89780f-ea30-442f-d502-def9196ea8bb" text="In parallel, the organization can conduct an internal confidential and anonymous survey to assess the scale of sexism existing in the working environment and to quantify the existing sexual and gender-based violence. This may also provide an opportunity to gather employees’ needs. Questionnaire templates are available.An analysis of the existing situation regarding sexual and gender-based violence is necessary in order to identify cases of violence and to launch an initiative to prevent sexual and gender-based violence in the organization. First, if this is not already the case, a risk assessment should be included in the organization’s global health and safety policy by adding a new section to the mandatory internal tool: the comprehensive occupational risk assessment." timestamp="1671533989213"?><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="9276395" change-id="6392b4cb-00c0-4f74-ec44-3e9edc3b286b" timestamp="1671533989516"?>A grievance mechanism is an accessible procedure or process that provides a clear and transparent framework for addressing grievances related to the organization and its workforce.<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="6392b4cb-00c0-4f74-ec44-3e9edc3b286b"?></p><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="9276395" change-id="21548635-7753-464f-f6f3-cd44cda43174" timestamp="1671533989516"?>A well-defined and communicated grievance mechanism contributes to the detection, prevention, and resolution of GBV, and the establishment of a safe work environment.<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="21548635-7753-464f-f6f3-cd44cda43174"?></p><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="9276395" change-id="582001c9-05c1-4eee-8661-606de16ec580" timestamp="1671533989516"?>An organization may require an internal grievance mechanism for its own workforce and possibly one for external stakeholders. Grievance procedures should be tailored to meet the needs of each organization, according to the sector, country, culture, workforce composition and its activities. There is no prescribed form or blueprint solution for grievance mechanisms.<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="582001c9-05c1-4eee-8661-606de16ec580"?></p></sec>